				First of newbs, in this game people like to go for rare and nice looking items. This robe looks like a Bloodstained Cryosilk robe, I waited  4 months to be able to loot mine. SECOND, when you have 220 Int you can cut down on some int items and replace them with AGI items or DEX items, like what I do. In my Case, I cut down on INT items till I was down to 200 int sharp and replaced the items with high level Cha and Wis items for jewelcraft. A 14 INT robe makes it all the better, So I can put my Steinof moggok away and hold a crude stein and a Mystic doll instead. If I was still stuck with my SMR, I would likely have to still hold onto some INT items where I could have had Cha or wis items. However this may be different for a Human, considering how stupid they are with a base of 110 int.. they need to get 90 Int and that is usually done with plane armor. My guildmate is a Human Wizard, Has some of the best Int items in the game, NICE 20+ int alone in his hand with staff of wheel and moggok.. has a Carmine robe and even has enough Int that he can wear his Serp bracers instead of GCBs. Hope this helps<BR>
