	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First off, hehe AGI gives you AC... I have 523 ac, as an Erudite Magician.<BR>
<BR>
Second, it`s so damn easy to max your int out. Humans, well that`s different. A human can max his int, and have higher than normal str and stamina.. making him alot tougher. I`m an Erudite, and have the apothic robe (won it random, after rolling 45, and being the winner lol)<BR>
<BR>
Second guys, before getting this robe, know this first.<BR>
<BR>
1) You have to be 46+ to enter the Plane of Hate<BR>
<BR>
2) You have to be welcomed by whoever is doing Hate then.. you cant just go up there and expect them to let you roll for loot.<BR>
<BR>
3) Most of the time you have to be in a level 40+ guild. My guild only accepts level 44+ members..<BR>
<BR>
4) You have invest ALOT of time doing Hate before they feel you deserve the robe. here`s my level dialog: 50, 49, 50, 49, 48, 47, 48, 47, 48, 49, 50, 49, 48, 49, 50... finally I got my robe =)<BR>
<BR>
5) This is a RARE drop. In order to increase my chances getting this robe, I passed on looting Apothic Leggings, and various other mage items. Eventually after 3 months of doing Hate every other night for hours, I got a tell from the event coordinator (sp) that I deserve the apothic robe, and told me to go ahead before a leech grabs it (a plooter).<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, this robe was my ultimate goal and dream since I found out about it. I was so happy I gave my SMR to a level 26 friend of mine who recently lost his corpse at 19, losing his Fbr.. he was happy about that too..<BR>
<BR>
Now, I am retired from the planes... I spend my time exploring Kunark or playing my level 18 Warrior twink.<BR>
<BR>
This robe is worth dying and losing levels for, its worth investing months into getting it.<BR>
<BR>
-Zakrell E'Jhanir<BR>
53 Erudite Elementalist
